the groundsman is a 2013 short film produced by the royal conservatoire of scotland . written & directed by jonny blair , starring david o'hara . the film depicts a lonely football groundsman named keith ( o'hara ) who finds out his club has gone out of business , but instead of moving on with his life and acknowledging his past affairs , he tries his utmost to keep the club running . the film screened for the first time at cineworld in glasgow on 20 june 2013 with the four other graduation films . in 2014 , the film was nominated for 3 bafta scotland new talent awards for best editing , best fiction and best writing . it went on to win best fiction and best editing .